@Node Usage "Usage"

  Usage
  =====

    This door has several modes of operation and can be started in
    three different ways.

    * If you press F6 when a user is online the following happens:

      The door will start, and message will be displayed to the user
      informing them the sysop is editing their account.

      The sysop can then modify the users account.  Changes made
      are permenant.

    * If you press SHIFT+F6 when a user is online the following
      happens:

      The door will start, and message will be displayed to the user
      informing them the sysop is editing their account.

      The sysop can then modify the users account.  Changes made
      are NOT permenant.  They will only last for the duration of the
      call.

    * If you press F6 when the await screen is displayed the sysop
      is presented with a menu, from which he can search for
      accounts to edit.

    Further Topics:

    @{"Validating a user" link ValidatingAUser}

@EndNode

@Node ValidatingAUser "Account Editor - Usage - Validating a user"

  Validating a user
  =================

    When you have the account information for the user on the screen
    do this:

    * Validating a new user to Sysop status

      Set the access level to 255

      Change other settings if you want to

      Press V to Validate your account. (See @{"AccountDefaults" link HBBS:Docs/Configuration/AccountDefaults.guide/MAIN})

      Press S to save and exit the account editor


    * Validating a new user to Normal status

      Set the access level to the normal user's access level (e.g. 50)
      (This level must have been defines in the HBBS:Access/Levels/Level_List file)

      Set the file upload/download ratio's accordingly.

      Set the users time allowed setting

      Press V to validate the account. (See @{"AccountDefaults" link HBBS:Docs/Configuration/AccountDefaults.guide/MAIN})

      Press S to save the account


@EndNode
